pt%20to%20breathe%20life%20into%20China's%20moribund%20property%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20immediate%20reaction%20from%20Wall%20Street%20was%20all-out%20jubilee.%20Since%20the%20pandemic%2C%20China's%20leader%2C%20Xi%20Jinping%2C%20has%20done%20little%20to%20stop%20the%20bleeding%20in%20the%20country's%20property%20market%20or%20to%20get%20China's%20ailing%20consumers%20to%20start%20spending%20money%20again.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Findex%2Fshanghai_composite%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EShanghai%20Composite%3C%2Fa%3E%20lost%20nearly%20a%20quarter%20of%20its%20value.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-xi-jinping-recession-economy-american-companies-profits-trade-war-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20companies%20in%20China%20are%20getting%20crushed%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Foreign%20investors%20are%20pulling%20record%20amounts%20of%20money%20out%20of%20the%20country.%20This%20week's%20announcements%20sent%20Wall%20Street%20into%20a%20state%20of%20rapture%2C%20hoping%20that%20the%20Chinese%20Communist%20Party%20is%20now%2C%20as%20in%20years%20past%2C%20prepared%20to%20catch%20a%20falling%20knife.%20The%20Golden%20Dragon%20index%20%E2%80%94%20a%20collection%20of%20Nasdaq-traded%20companies%20that%20do%20most%20of%20their%20business%20in%20China%20%E2%80%94%20rallied%209%25%20following%20the%20announcements.%20Financial-news%20talking%20heads%20heralded%20this%20as%20a%20clear%20sign%20from%20Beijing%20that%20policymakers%20were%20getting%20real%20about%20stopping%20China's%20descent%20into%20a%20deflationary%20funk.%20There%20would%20be%20more%20mergers%20and%20acquisitions!%20Lower%20rates%20could%20mean%20more%20private-equity%20activity!%20The%20famous%20Beijing%20%26quot%3Bbazooka%26quot%3B%20could%20finally%20be%20on%20the%20way!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20honey%2C%20they%20are%20delusional.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EXi's%20Beijing%20lacks%20the%20will%20and%20the%20power%20to%20turn%20China's%20economy%20around.%20At%20the%20heart%20of%20its%20problems%20is%20a%20lack%20of%20consumer%20demand%20and%20a%20property%20market%20going%20through%20a%20deep%2C%20slow-moving%20correction.%20Xi%20is%20ideologically%20opposed%20to%20jump-starting%20consumer%20spending%20with%20direct%20stimulus%20checks.%20No%20will.%20As%20for%20the%20power%2C%20Goldman%20Sachs%20estimated%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2024-04-15%2Fchina-real-estate-crisis-private-builders-face-553-billion-gap-to-finish-homes%3Fsref%3DE0nAM78N%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereturning%20China's%20apartment%20inventory%20to%202018%20levels%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20require%207.7%20trillion%20yuan.%20China's%20property%20market%20is%20so%20overbuilt%20and%20indebted%20that%20the%20trillions%20in%20stimulus%20needed%20to%20fix%20the%20problem%20%E2%80%94%20and%20make%20the%20local%20governments%20that%20financed%20it%20whole%20again%20%E2%80%94%20would%20make%20even%20a%20rapacious%20fundraiser%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-sam-altman-wants-seven-trillion-openai-compare-costs-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%20blush%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20%26quot%3Bstimulus%26quot%3B%20China's%20policymakers%20are%20offering%20is%20a%20drop%20in%20a%20well%2C%20and%20they%20know%20that.%20Wall%20Street%20should%20too.%20But%20I%20guess%20they%20haven't%20learned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20measures%20the%20CCP%20announced%20are%20intended%20to%20make%20it%20easier%20for%20Chinese%20people%20to%20access%20capital%20and%20buy%20property%2C%20but%20access%20to%20debt%20is%20not%20the%20problem%20here.%20People%20in%20the%20country%20do%20not%20want%20to%20spend%20money%20because%20they%20are%20already%20sitting%20on%20large%20amounts%20of%20real-estate%20debt%20tied%20to%20declining%20properties.%20Seventy%20percent%20of%20Chinese%20household%20wealth%20is%20invested%20in%20property%2C%20which%20is%20a%20problem%20since%20analysts%20at%20Soci%C3%A9t%C3%A9%20Gen%C3%A9ral%C3%A9%20found%20that%20housing%20prices%20have%20fallen%20by%20as%20much%20as%2030%25%20in%20Tier%201%20cities%20since%20their%202021%20peak.%20Land%20purchases%20helped%20fund%20local%20governments%20so%20they%20could%20spend%20on%20schools%2C%20hospitals%2C%20and%20other%20social%20services%20%E2%80%94%20now%20that%20financing%20mechanism%20is%20out%20of%20whack.%20Sinking%20prices%20in%20these%20sectors%2C%20or%20what%20economists%20call%20deflation%2C%20has%20spread%20to%20the%20wider%20economy.%20The%20latest%20consumer%20price%20inflation%20report%20showed%20that%20prices%20rose%20by%20just%200.3%25%20in%20August%20compared%20to%20the%20year%20before%2C%20the%20lowest%20price%20growth%20in%20three%20years%2C%20prompting%20concerns%20that%20deflation%20will%20take%20hold%2C%20spreading%20to%20wages%20and%20killing%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20that%20context%2C%20many%20Chinese%20people%20are%20not%20eager%20to%20spend.%20Consumers%20are%20trading%20down%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-economy-so-bad-people-wont-buy-cheap-alibaba-items-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echeaper%20products%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20second-quarter%20retail%20sales%20grew%20by%20only%202.7%25%20from%20the%20previous%20year.%20In%20a%20recent%20note%20to%20clients%2C%20the%20business%20surveyor%20China%20Beige%20Book%20said%20that%20business%20borrowing%20had%20barely%20budged%20since%20all-time%20lows%20in%202021%2C%20during%20the%20depths%20of%20the%20pandemic.%20Bottom%20line%3A%20It%20doesn't%20matter%20how%20cheap%20and%20easy%20it%20is%20to%20access%20loans%20if%20no%20one%20wants%20to%20take%20one%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20mostly%20supply-side%20measures%20would%20certainly%20be%20helpful%20if%20the%20problem%20in%20China%20was%20that%20production%20was%20struggling%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20growth%20in%20demand%2C%26quot%3B%20Michael%20Pettis%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20finance%20at%20Peking%20University%20and%20a%20Carnegie%20Endowment%20fellow%2C%20said%20in%20a%20recent%20post%20on%20X.%20%26quot%3BBut%20with%20weak%20demand%20as%20the%20main%20constraint%2C%20these%20measures%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20boost%20the%20trade%20surplus%20than%20GDP%20growth.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20direct%20way%20to%20spur%20demand%20in%20a%20deflating%20economy%20is%20to%20send%20checks%20to%20households.%20But%20again%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-xi-jinping-recession-economy-american-companies-profits-trade-war-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EXi%20doesn't%20want%20to%20do%20that%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20Chinese%20president%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.nytimes.com%2Fsinosphere.blogs.nytimes.com%2F2013%2F10%2F30%2Fa-lonely-passion-chinas-followers-of-friedrich-a-hayek%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eis%20a%20follower%20of%20the%20Austrian%20economist%20Friedrich%20Hayek%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20believed%20that%20direct%20stimulus%20distorts%20markets%20and%20leads%20to%20uncontrollable%20inflation.%20This%20flies%20in%20the%20face%20of%20what%20economists%20would%20recommend%20for%20China's%20situation%2C%20but%20those%20who%20criticize%20the%20way%20Xi%20does%20things%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzhu-hengpeng-china-economist-disappears-after-criticizing-xi-jinping-wechat-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etend%20to%20disappear%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20clear%20that%20Beijing's%20recent%20moves%20won't%20solve%20China's%20core%20economic%20problems.%20And%20Wall%20Street's%20excitement%20misses%20another%20key%20problem%3A%20The%20measures%20aren't%20even%20all%20that%20big.%20Call%20it%20a%20bazooka%20or%20a%20blitz%20or%20whatever%2C%20but%20this%20stimulus%20is%20tiny%20compared%20with%20what%20we've%20seen%20from%20the%20CCP%20in%20the%20past.%20In%202009%2C%20the%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fget-ready-for-a-epic-stimulus-spending-out-of-china-in-the-final-couple-weeks-of-december-2009-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edropped%207.6%20trillion%20yuan%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20save%20the%20economy%20during%20the%20global%20financial%20crisis.%20In%202012%2C%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fbusiness%2Fchina-approves-157-billion-infrastructure-spending-idUSBRE88613D%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edropped%20%24157%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20infrastructure%20projects.%20In%202015%2C%20it%20injected%20over%20%24100%20billion%20into%20ailing%20regional%20banks%20and%20devalued%20its%20currency%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-currency-devaluation-a-sign-of-weakness-2015-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eboost%20flagging%20exports%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20CCP%20has%20shown%20that%20it's%20willing%20to%20take%20dramatic%20action%20to%20stabilize%20the%20economy.%20The%20price%20of%20that%20action%2C%20though%2C%20is%20massive%20debt%20built%20up%20all%20over%20the%20financial%20system%2C%20held%20especially%20by%20property%20companies%2C%20state-owned%20enterprises%2C%20and%20local%20governments.%20In%20the%20past%2C%20monetary%20easing%20calmed%20gyrations%20in%20the%20financial%20system%2C%20but%20growth%20has%20never%20been%20this%20slow%2C%20and%20debt%20has%20never%20been%20this%20high.%20The%20problem%20does%20not%20match%20the%20price%20tag%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese%20Communist%20Party%20has%20a%20bubble%20on%20its%20hands%2C%20and%20it%20doesn't%20want%20to%20blow%20much%20more%20or%20see%20it%20burst%20in%20spectacular%20fashion.%20Plus%2C%20there's%20Xi%2C%20who%20seems%20fairly%20uninterested%20in%20restructuring%20the%20property%20market.%20He%20wants%20government%20investment%20to%20focus%20on%20developing%20frontier%20technology%20and%20boosting%20exports%20to%20grow%20the%20economy%20out%20of%20its%20structural%20debt%20problems.%20But%20those%20new%20streams%20of%20income%20have%20yet%20to%20materialize%20for%20China%2C%20and%20establishing%20them%20will%20take%20time%20and%20working%20through%20trade%20conflict%2C%20principally%20with%20the%20US%20and%20the%20European%20Union.%20Consider%20the%20easing%20measures%20we're%20seeing%20as%20something%20like%20a%20moment%20for%20markets%20to%20catch%20their%20breath%20%E2%80%94%20a%20respite%20from%20what%20has%20been%20a%20constant%20stream%20of%20bad%20economic%20news.%20But%20a%20respite%20is%20all%20it%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Flinette-lopez%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3ELinette%20Lopez%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-xi-jinping-stimulus-plan-wall-street-stock-market-economy-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727603822000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66f6f6fcf9f6733e4be06753%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-xi-jinping-stimulus-plan-wall-street-stock-market-economy-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Wall%20Street%20ate%20up%20China's%20newest%20plan%20to%20jump-start%20their%20economy.%20But%20Xi%20Jinping's%20ideas%20won't%20fix%20the%20country's%20biggest%20problems.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22llopez%40insider.com%20(Linette%20Lopez)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-xi-jinping-stimulus-plan-wall-street-stock-market-economy-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%225%20of%20my%20favorite%20features%20on%20the%20Chevrolet%20Equinox%20EV%20that%2