EOs%2C%20which%20found%20that%20only%2034%25%20expected%20workers%20to%20return%20full-time%20to%20their%20on-site%20desks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20shift%20in%20their%20attitude%20flies%20in%20the%20face%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-work-good-for-productivity-here-to-stay-pwc-2024-9%23%3A~%3Atext%3D%2522Hybrid%2520workers%2520have%2520higher%2520degrees%2Cat%2520PwC%252C%2520told%2520Business%2520Insider.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edata%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhybrid-work-flexibility-not-rto-may-help-companies-boost-sales-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexpert%20warnings%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftell-dell-annual-survey-results-show-employees-frustration-rto-push-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemployees%3C%2Fa%3E%20themselves%20who%20insist%20that%20having%20some%20flexibility%20in%20their%20working%20life%20is%20good%20for%20them%20and%20the%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20why%20do%20some%20CEOs%20who%20spend%20their%20days%20strategizing%20how%20to%20boost%20productivity%20and%20generate%20profits%20not%20listen%20to%20these%20arguments%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrigid%20Schulte%2C%20journalist%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Better%20Life%20Lab%2C%20and%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BOver%20Work%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20it's%20because%20they're%20operating%20in%20an%20%26quot%3Becho%20chamber.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BReturn%20to%20office%20is%20so%20based%20on%20a%20leader's%20belief%2C%26quot%3B%20Schulte%20explained.%20%26quot%3BIt%20has%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20the%20evidence.%20It%20often%20has%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20the%20performance%20and%20who's%20a%20really%20good%20worker%20or%20innovative%20or%20coming%20up%20with%20great%20ideas.%20It%20all%20has%20to%20do%20with%20confirmation%20bias.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToo%20many%20leaders%20simply%20think%20the%20way%20they%20achieved%20success%20is%20the%20best%20way%20to%20work%20and%20it's%20all%20they're%20comfortable%20with%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20think%20businesses%20want%20to%20be%20efficient%20and%20effective%20and%20profitable%2C%20it%20is%20mystifying%20to%20me%20how%20powerful%20that%20leadership%20mindset%20and%20belief%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20Schulte%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20resistance%20to%20new%20approaches%20is%20reinforced%20when%20they%20talk%20to%20each%20other%20and%20see%20others%20making%20declarations%20to%20the%20media%2C%20Schulte%20continued%2C%20describing%20that%20pattern%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bcircular%20echo%20chamber.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20do%20worry%20that%20more%20are%20looking%20at%20the%20boldness%20of%20these%20return-to-office%20mandates%20and%20thinking%2C%20well%2C%20if%20they%20did%20it%2C%20I%20can%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Andy%20Jassy%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654b65b93cc84b4dfafe5c44%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BThe%20advantages%20of%20being%20together%20in%20the%20office%20are%20significant%2C%26quot%3B%20Amazon%20CEO%20Andy%20Jassy%20wrote%20in%20a%20memo%20announcing%20the%20new%20RTO%20policy.%3Cp%3EThos%20Robinson%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWorsening%20that%20echo%20chamber%20structure%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20CEOs%20are%20%26quot%3Blargely%20white%20men%2C%26quot%3B%20Schulte%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMany%20of%20them%20have%20either%20virtually%20no%20care%20responsibilities%20or%20have%20somebody%20else%20taking%20care%20of%20them.%20So%20they%20have%20been%20able%20to%20devote%20themselves%20150%25%20to%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchulte%20said%20it's%20no%20surprise%20that%20some%20of%20the%20worst%20offenders%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20strict%20RTO%20mandates%20are%20in%20%26quot%3Bvery%20male-dominated%20overwork%20cultures%2C%20like%20finance%2C%20tech%2C%20and%20law.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ce27c4db-3e9c-4019-91bb-205387efac9e%5C%22%3EPop%20the%20echo%20chamber%20bubble%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESchulte's%20research%20for%20the%20book%20showed%20her%20that%20many%20companies%20had%20taken%20advantage%20of%20the%20disruptions%20caused%20by%20COVID%20to%20rethink%20their%20methods%20and%20make%20positive%20and%20lasting%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20started%20by%20talking%20down%20to%20the%20people%20in%20their%20organization%2C%20not%20just%20in%20this%20rarefied%20bubble%20of%20the%20C-suite%2C%26quot%3B%20Schulte%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20there%20is%20not%20a%20one-size-fits-all%20outcome%3B%20organizations%20are%20different%20and%20have%20different%20cultures%20and%20priorities.%20But%20what's%20key%20is%20that%20leaders%20are%20willing%20to%20listen%20and%20act.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20that's%20not%20forthcoming%20from%20your%20CEO%2C%20there%20are%20things%20you%20can%20do%20as%20an%20individual%20and%20an%20organization%20to%20bring%20about%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRun%20an%20internal%20pilot%2C%20gather%20your%20own%20data%2C%20make%20the%20case%2C%20and%20continue%20to%20make%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Schulte%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20important%20to%20acknowledge%20that%20working%20effectively%20in%20a%20digital%20work%20environment%20means%20you%20have%20to%20be%20much%20more%20explicit%20about%20tasks%2C%20transparent%20in%20communication%2C%20and%20have%20a%20clear%20accountability%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20that%20echo%20chamber%2C%20a%20couple%20of%20brave%20leaders%20are%20going%20to%20have%20to%20be%20willing%20to%20do%20something%20differently%2C%20but%20it%20can%20definitely%20happen%2C%20Schulte%20said.%20Some%20of%20the%20CEOs%20she%20spoke%20to%20have%20had%20%26quot%3Baha%20moments.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%