sting%20an%20offensive%20before%20a%20breakthrough.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAn%20influential%20think%20tank%20believes%20it%20has%20a%20solution%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20going%20to%20be%20easy.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BFirepower%20kills%2C%26quot%3B%20warned%20the%20French%20General%20Philippe%20P%C3%A9tain%20just%20prior%20to%20the%20First%20World%20War.%20He%20worried%20that%20the%20would-be%20Napoleons%20of%201914%2C%20who%20dreamed%20of%20sweeping%20maneuvers%20and%20crushing%20victories%2C%20ignored%20a%20crucial%20possibility%3A%20that%20troops%20moving%20in%20the%20open%20would%20be%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thefreelibrary.com%2FMarshal%2BPetain%2BUnderstood%2BIt%2BAll%253A%2BFirepower%2BKills.-a076736954%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emown%20down%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%20artillery%20and%20machine%20guns.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EP%C3%A9tain%20was%20proved%20right%3A%20firepower%20became%20so%20lethal%20that%20the%20armies%20of%20World%20War%20I%20dug%20deeply%20into%20the%20earth%20just%20to%20survive%2C%20until%20new%20weapons%20%E2%80%94%20notably%20the%20tank%20%E2%80%94%20broke%20the%20trench%20deadlock.%20But%20a%20century%20later%2C%20warfare%20has%20come%20full%20circle%3A%20drones%2C%20artillery%20and%20guided%20munitions%20have%20made%20movement%20so%20hazardous%20that%20both%20armies%20in%20Ukraine%20have%20reverted%20to%20trench%20warfare.%20Even%20Ukrainian%20forces%20in%20the%20recent%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newsweek.com%2Fukraine-kursk-offensive-500-square-miles-russia-kyiv-1944894%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EKursk%20offensive%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20which%20used%20mechanized%20maneuver%20to%20seize%20nearly%20500%20miles%20of%20Russian%20territory%2C%20are%20now%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kyivpost.com%2Fpost%2F37252%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edigging%20in%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhether%20in%201914%20or%202024%2C%20there%20is%20a%20downside%20to%20a%20firepower-centric%20strategy%3A%20it%20tends%20to%20lead%20toward%20indecisive%20battles%20of%20attrition.%20Firepower%20can%20sweep%20the%20ground%2C%20but%20it%20can't%20occupy%20it.%20At%20some%20point%2C%20victory%20requires%20offensive%20maneuver%20to%20encircle%20opposing%20forces%20and%20sever%20supply%20lines.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20is%20a%20maneuver%20strategy%20even%20possible%20anymore%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20US%20think%20tank%20believes%20it%20has%20a%20solution%20for%20Ukraine%20as%20well%20as%20better%20armed%20Western%20militaries.%20By%20temporarily%20suppressing%20the%20defensive%20drone-artillery%20combo%20that%20has%20proven%20so%20devastating%20in%20the%20Russo-Ukraine%20War%2C%20armies%20can%20again%20maneuver%20to%20defeat%20their%20enemies.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BThis%20task%20is%20feasible%2C%26quot%3B%20argues%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.understandingwar.org%2Fbackgrounder%2Fukraine-and-problem-restoring-maneuver-contemporary-war%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereport%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%20the%20Washington-based%20Institute%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20War.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BIt%20requires%20imagination%2C%20innovation%2C%20and%20iteration.%20It%20requires%20experimentation%20with%20battlefield%20concepts%20as%20well%20as%20with%20technology%20and%20tactics.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EISW%20sees%20three%20problems%20with%20trying%20to%20maneuver%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20lessons%20that%20broadly%20apply%20to%20modern%20battlefields.%20First%2C%20Ukraine%20and%20Russia%20field%20armies%20large%20enough%20to%20cover%20the%20front%20without%20leaving%20gaps%20or%20open%20flanks%2C%20which%20means%20that%20an%20attacker%20usually%20has%20to%20assault%20through%20fortified%20lines%20(the%20study%20was%20written%20prior%20to%20Ukraine's%20thrust%20across%20the%20little-defended%20Russian%20border%20into%20Kursk).%20But%20drones%2C%20artillery%2C%20mines%20and%20other%20weapons%20have%20made%20penetrating%20enemy%20defenses%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-the-ukrainian-counteroffensive-ran-into-trouble-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eso%20costly%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20the%20attacker%20becomes%20too%20exhausted%20to%20exploit%20a%20breakthrough.%20And%20even%20if%20the%20attacker%20can%20punch%20a%20hole%2C%20the%20defender%20usually%20has%20enough%20resources%20to%20build%20fortified%20positions%2C%20sealing%20off%20the%20penetration%20and%20forcing%20the%20attacker%20to%20repeat%20the%20process.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Artillery%20and%20machine%20guns%20were%20so%20deadly%20in%20World%20War%20I%20that%20armies%20fought%20from%20trenches.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66f7016af9f6733e4be0746e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221516%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EArtillery%20and%20machine%20guns%20were%20so%20deadly%20in%20World%20War%20I%20that%20armies%20fought%20from%20trenches.%3Cp%3EUniversal%20History%20Archive%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20exactly%20describes%20the%20situation%20on%20the%20First%20World%20War's%20Western%20Front%2C%20a%20comparison%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.economist.com%2Fby-invitation%2F2023%2F11%2F01%2Fthe-commander-in-chief-of-ukraines-armed-forces-on-how-to-win-the-war%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emade%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%20Ukraine's%20top%20general%20after%20the%202023%20counter-offensive.%20But%20modern%20technology%20has%20added%20a%20new%20twist%3A%20drones%20and%20guided%20munition%20in%20what%20ISW%20calls%20%E2%80%94%20based%20on%20a%20Cold%20War-era%20Soviet%20concept%20%E2%80%94%20the%20%26quot%3Btactical%20reconnaissance%20strike%20complex.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BThe%20TRSC%20is%20the%20combination%20of%20pervasive%20tactical%20reconnaissance%2C%20primarily%20by%20drone%3B%20drone-corrected%20precision%20artillery%20fire%3B%20precision%20munitions%20delivered%20by%20fixed-%20and%2For%20rotary-wing%20aircraft%3B%20drone-launched%20precision%20munitions%3B%20and%20large%20numbers%20of%20FPV%20%5Bfirst-person%20view%5D%20loitering%20munitions%2C%26quot%3B%20ISW%20explained.%20While%20both%20the%20attacker%20and%20defender%20can%20use%20the%20TRSC%2C%20it%20is%20the%20attacker%20who%20must%20break%20cover%20and%20expose%20himself%20in%20the%20open.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20this%20conception%2C%20the%20TRSC%20is%20dynamic%2C%20a%20cat-and-mouse%20game%20where%20each%20side%20seeks%20to%20jam%20the%20links%20between%20enemy%20drones%20and%20their%20operators%2C%20while%20constantly%20updating%20their%20own%20drone%20systems%20to%20beat%20jamming.%20For%20Ukraine%20%E2%80%94%20or%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%20to%20launch%20successful%20ground%20offensives%2C%20it%20will%20need%20to%20exploit%20%26quot%3Bfleeting%20technological%20advantages%20to%20disrupt%20the%20defender's%20TRSC%20in%20support%20of%20the%20initial%20penetration%20operation%20and%20to%20sustain%20the%20advantage%20long%20enough%20to%20create%20a%20moving%20envelope%20that%20protects%20exploitation%20forces%20through%20to%20their%20planned%20culmination%20and%20transition%20to%20the%20defensive%20having%20secured%20their%20objectives.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20the%20assault%20force%20needs%20to%20be%20protected%20by%20jammers%20and%20air%20defenses%20as%20it%20rumbles%20a%20path%20through%20the%20enemy's%20defe